-- 
Copper in London Drops for the First Time in Three Days

-- B y   G l e n y s   S i m
-- 
2011-02-28T01:05:07Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-28/copper-in-london-drops-for-the-first-time-in-three-days-on-mideast-concern.html
Copper in  London  dropped for the
first time in three days on concern the turmoil which began in
Egypt and has cut oil output in  Libya  may spread to other parts
of the Middle East, driving energy prices higher and weigh on
global growth.  The metal for three-month delivery on the London Metal
Exchange fell as much as 0.6 percent to $9,705 a metric ton, and
traded at $9,714 by 9:03 a.m. Singapore time. Futures in
Shanghai gained for a second day, by as much as 1 percent, to
73,300 yuan a ton.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Glenys Sim at 
 gsim4@bloomberg.net  